    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Name: {{ $json.name }}\nEmail: {{ $json.email }}\nMessage: {{ $json.message }}\nSource: {{ $json.source }}",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "You are a lead qualification assistant. Given a lead's name, email, message, and source, output a JSON assessment.\n\nScore 1-10:\n1-2: not a lead (spam, recruiter pitch, vendor cold-pitch, junk/empty)\n3-4: low quality (vague, one-word, no real need shown)\n5-6: moderate (some interest, thin on detail)\n7-8: good (clear need, realistic scope, genuine intent)\n9-10: high priority (urgency, budget/timeline, explicit ask for call/quote)\n\nIntent (pick one): genuine_inquiry, vague_interest, spam_or_pitch, not_a_lead\n\nRules:\n- Any message under 5 words, empty, or URL-only MUST score 4 or below, no exceptions. Urgent-sounding words (\"now\", \"asap\", \"urgent\") do NOT override this — urgency without a stated need is still a thin message, not a high-priority one.\n- A message only counts as high priority (9-10) if it states an actual need, service, project, or problem AND shows urgency/budget/timeline. Urgency language alone, with no stated need, caps at 4.\n- Partnership/vendor/service-offering pitches → spam_or_pitch, regardless of tone.\n- Non-English messages: judge content, don't penalize for language.\n- Ignore forwarded/signature/thread boilerplate; judge only the human-written inquiry.\n- Never infer unstated name/need/urgency; missing info lowers score, don't fill gaps.\n- Do not alter, correct, or reformat the name, email, or source — copy them exactly as given in the input, even if they look malformed.\n- Invalid or malformed email addresses (missing @, no domain, commas instead of periods, random strings) → score 2 or below, intent: not_a_lead, regardless of message content. Copy the email exactly as given.\n\nOutput rules:\n- Respond with ONLY the final JSON object below. Nothing else.\n- Do not repeat, echo, quote, or reference any schema, instructions, or formatting rules in your response.\n- Do not include markdown code fences (no ```).\n- Output exactly one JSON object, nothing before or after it.\n\n{\"name\": \"<copy from input>\", \"email\": \"<copy from input>\", \"source\": \"<copy from input>\", \"score\": <1-10>, \"intent\": \"<category>\", \"summary\": \"<one sentence>\"}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [
        1296,
        240
      ],
      "id": "05cd6219-3370-4626-971e-4c2d7a6c6c33",
